-- Prime Minister Kan's Approval Rating Falls to 40%, Sankei Newspaper Says
-- Kazuyo Sawa
-- 2010-07-19T22:32:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/prime-minister-kan-s-approval-rating-falls-to-40-sankei-newspaper-says.html

          
          
             Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan
has an approval rating of 40.3 percent in a Sankei newspaper
survey taken July 17-18, down 3.3 percentage points from July 3-
4. His disapproval rating rose 5.1 points to 45.8 percent.  
 The governing Democratic Party of Japan has popular support
of 28 percent, down 1.9 points. The support level for the
opposition Liberal Democratic Party rose 2.4 points to 18.7
percent, the newspaper said.  
